# Cleanup Standards

Automated enforcement: `./gradlew detekt ktlintCheck` must pass before any commit.

## No Magic Numbers

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
if (batteryLevel < 15) switchToSurvivalMode()
if (riders.size > 4) enableClustering()
val interval = 5000L

// ✅ GOOD -- named constants in RouteConstants or feature-specific companion object
object SlickConstants {
    const val SURVIVAL_MODE_BATTERY_THRESHOLD = 15
    const val CONVOY_CLUSTERING_THRESHOLD = 4
    const val BLE_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL_MS = 10_000L
    const val NODE_INTERVAL_KM = 10.0
    const val MAX_DETOUR_RADIUS_KM = 15.0
    const val THERMAL_THROTTLE_CELSIUS = 40.0
    const val THERMAL_CRITICAL_CELSIUS = 45.0
    const val SOS_COUNTDOWN_SECONDS = 60
    const val GPS_BATCH_SURVIVAL_MS = 30_000L
    const val PACK_BROADCAST_INTERVAL_MS = 5_000L   // 0.2 Hz
    const val LEAD_BROADCAST_INTERVAL_MS = 1_000L    // 1 Hz
}
```

## No Hardcoded URLs or IDs

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
val url = "https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast"
val serviceId = "com.slick.tactical.mesh.v1"

// ✅ GOOD -- from BuildConfig (injected via secrets-gradle-plugin)
val baseUrl = BuildConfig.OPEN_METEO_BASE_URL
val serviceId = BuildConfig.P2P_SERVICE_ID
```

## Logging Standards (Timber Only)

### Banned — never use these:
```kotlin
Log.d("TAG", "message")     // ❌ raw Android log
Log.e("TAG", "error", e)    // ❌ raw Android log
println("debug info")       // ❌
System.out.println(...)     // ❌
```

### Required — Timber only:
```kotlin
Timber.d("Node loaded: %s nodeId=%s", nodeType, nodeId)   // ✅
Timber.e(exception, "Sync failed: %s", reason)             // ✅
```

### Timber Level Guidelines

| Level | When to use | Example | Reaches Sentry? |
|-------|-------------|---------|-----------------|
| `Timber.v()` | Sensor frame-by-frame data (very noisy, dev only) | IMU sample value | Never |
| `Timber.d()` | Fine-grained lifecycle and state changes | GPS batch received, node sliced | Never |
| `Timber.i()` | System lifecycle milestones | Service started, sync complete, convoy joined | Never |
| `Timber.w()` | Recoverable issues, fallback paths used | Valhalla unavailable, API fallback used | **Yes (staging + release)** |
| `Timber.e()` | Errors that degrade functionality | Crash detection failed, DB insert failed | **Yes (all builds with crash reporting)** |

**Rule: if in doubt, use `Timber.w()` not `Timber.e()`.**  
`Timber.e()` means "user noticed something broken." `Timber.w()` means "we handled it gracefully."

### PII Rules — Mandatory

These fields MUST NEVER appear in any `Timber.w()` or `Timber.e()` call:

```kotlin
// ❌ BANNED in WARN/ERROR logs
Timber.e("GPS error at lat=%.4f lon=%.4f", location.lat, location.lon)
Timber.w("Rider %s dropped out", fullRiderName)

// ✅ ALLOWED -- anonymised, no coordinates, no real IDs
Timber.e("GPS error at [GPS_REDACTED]")
Timber.w("Rider [id=%s] dropped out", shortEphemeralId.take(4))
Timber.i("GPS fix: %.4f, %.4f", lat, lon)  // INFO never reaches Sentry -- safe
```

`SlickCrashTree` applies regex scrubbing to GPS coordinates and rider IDs before any message
reaches Sentry, but defence-in-depth requires you to NOT include them in the first place.

### Build Type → Logging Matrix

| Build | `ENABLE_DEBUG_LOGGING` | `ENABLE_CRASH_REPORTING` | Timber trees active |
|-------|------------------------|--------------------------|---------------------|
| `debug` | true | false | `DebugTree` (all levels, file + line) |
| `staging` | true | true | `DebugTree` + `SlickCrashTree` |
| `release` | false | true | `SlickCrashTree` only (WARN+ to Sentry) |

### Sentry Crash Reporting

Sentry is initialised in `SlickApplication.initialiseSentry()`.  
DSN is set in `local.properties` (`SENTRY_DSN=`).  
Create an Android project at https://kuschmierz.sentry.io to get the DSN.

Configuration in `SlickApplication`:
- `isSendDefaultPii = false` — no IP addresses, no device names
- `tracesSampleRate = 0.0` — performance monitoring disabled (battery cost)
- `isAnrEnabled = true` — catches Application Not Responding events

## KDoc on All Public Functions

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD -- undocumented public API
fun haversineDistance(lat1: Double, lon1: Double, lat2: Double, lon2: Double): Double

// ✅ GOOD
/**
 * Calculates great-circle distance between two GPS coordinates.
 * Uses the Haversine formula with Earth radius = 6371.0 km.
 *
 * @return Distance in kilometres
 */
fun haversineDistance(lat1: Double, lon1: Double, lat2: Double, lon2: Double): Double
```

## No Empty Files

Files with 0 lines or only `package` declaration should be deleted.

## No Duplicate Utilities

Before creating a new utility function, search for existing:
- `util/Haversine.kt` -- distance calculations
- `util/MetricConverter.kt` -- unit conversions
- `util/ResultExtensions.kt` -- Result<T> helpers
- `util/TimeFormatter.kt` -- 24h time formatting

## File Size Enforcement

Check with detekt or manual review:

| Type | Max Lines | Violation Action |
|------|-----------|-----------------|
| Service | 400 | Extract engine component |
| Composable screen | 250 | Extract sub-composables |
| ViewModel | 300 | Extract use case classes |
| Repository | 300 | Split by data source |
| Engine Manager | 400 | Extract strategy classes |
| Utility | 150 | Split by concern |

## Pre-Commit Checklist

Run before every git commit:
```bash
./gradlew ktlintCheck          # Kotlin style
./gradlew detekt               # Static analysis
./gradlew test                 # Unit tests
./gradlew assembleDebug        # Build check
```
